name: Park Animal Hospital Massapequa
overview:
Park Animal Hospital is a family-owned and operated veterinary hospital located in Massapequa, New York. Offering high-quality veterinary medicine and surgery services, the hospital focuses on treating dogs, cats, rabbits, small rodents, and reptiles. The veterinary professionals practicing at the hospital hold extensive experience in a complete range of veterinary services, from annual examinations and vaccinations to soft tissue surgeries and dental procedures. Committed to staying current with modern trends in veterinary medicine, Park Animal Hospital in Massapequa also offers state-of-the-art procedures such as DNA testing and stem cell therapy.

Founded in 1980, Park Animal Hospital is overseen by original founders Dr. H. James Schroll and Dr. Jane Sparacino. Established members of the veterinary profession, doctors maintain affiliations with the International Association of Aquatic Animal Medicine as well as the American Veterinary Medical Association. Further information regarding the services offered by the veterinary center can be found online at www.massapequaparkanimalhospital.com.
